<subSubSection id="C337088DF77BB13AB182FE483016417F" pageId="14" pageNumber="535" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F77BB13AB182FE483016417F" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">
COMMENTS: The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F77BB13AB08CFE48305A4293" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1844" box="[457,611,439,465]" class="Aves" family="Ploceidae" genus="Hyphantornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="535" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9598714F77BB13AB08CFE48305A4293" box="[457,611,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">Hyphantornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77BB13AB27DFE4831804293" author="Gray, G. R." box="[824,953,439,465]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535" refId="ref28601" refString="Gray, G. R. (1844 - 1849) The Genera of Birds Comprising their Generic Characters, a Notice of the Habits of Each Genus, and an Extensive List of Species Referred to their Several Genera. 3 Vols. Longman, Brown, Green, and Longmans, London. [unpaginated] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 126497" type="book" year="1844">Gray (1844</bibRefCitation>
–1849) in volume 2 of his Genera of birds on page 350, according to the “Contents of the second volume” but it is actually not paginated. Sundevall corrected the spelling to 
<emphasis id="B9598714F77BB13AB07AFE0033DE415B" box="[319,487,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">Hyphanthornis</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77BB13AB0B3FE003133415B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[502,778,511,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 12)</bibRefCitation>
used 
<emphasis id="B9598714F77BB13AB209FE0031CD415B" box="[844,1012,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">Hyphanthornis</emphasis>
, but Gray’s (linguistically erroneous) spelling is valid following the Code.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
